#: ../../W/well-behaved.rst:5
msgid "well-behaved"
msgstr "well-behaved"

#: ../../W/well-behaved.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../W/well-behaved.rst:10
msgid ""
"Software that does its job quietly and without counterintuitive effects. "
"Esp. : said of software having an interface spec sufficiently simple and "
"well-defined that it can be used as a :ref:`tool` by other software. See "
":ref:`cat`\\."
msgstr ""
"直感に反する作用なしに、静かに仕事をこなすソフトウェア。特に、インターフェイス仕様が十分に単純かつ明確に定義されており、他のソフトウェアによって\\ "
":ref:`tool`\\ として使えるソフトウェアについて言う。\\ :ref:`cat`\\ を参照。"

#: ../../W/well-behaved.rst:16
msgid ""
"Said of an algorithm that doesn't :ref:`crash` or :ref:`blow-up`\\, even "
"when given :ref:`pathological` input. Implies that the stability of the "
"algorithm is intrinsic, which makes this somewhat different from "
":ref:`bulletproof`\\."
msgstr ""
"\\ :ref:`pathological`\\ な入力を与えられても\\ :ref:`crash`\\ したり\\ :ref:`blow-up`\\ "
"したりしないアルゴリズムについて言う。アルゴリズムの安定性が本質的であることを含意し、これが\\ :ref:`bulletproof`\\ "
"とはいくらか異なる点である。"
